The paper deals with a problem of maximizing social welfare by allocating items to agents, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). The problem involves submodular functions, which are commonly studied in algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the online version of the problem, which is a topic in machine learning and online algorithms (cs.LG). The application of the problem to Internet advertising suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper involves analysis of algorithms and competitive ratios, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT).
